  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Can gzip be a language model?",
      "url": "https://nathan.rs/posts/gzip-lm/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/j11pew",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "AviKav",
      "published": "2026-06-16T22:17:20Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Using gzip, Normalized Compression Distance (NCD), and k-NN enables parameter-free text classification without training heavy deep learning models.",
        "This compression-based approach rivals models like BERT on out-of-distribution datasets while requiring zero parameters or GPU training.",
        "However, execution scales poorly to large datasets due to the O(N^2) complexity of pairwise compression and k-NN search."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "But yak shaving is fun",
      "url": "https://parksb.github.io/en/article/32.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/zpjomk",
      "score": 13,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "hoistbypetard",
      "published": "2026-06-16T19:18:46Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Deep toolchain setups (like Nix, Docker, or Webpack) offer learning value but often become massive productivity sinks disguised as engineering work.",
        "Building custom internal developer tooling improves developer experience but creates long-term maintenance overhead instead of leveraging existing SaaS alternatives.",
        "Engineers must timebox system optimizations, balancing the educational joy of solving peripheral technical problems against pragmatic product shipping velocities."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Honda Civics and the Evil Valet",
      "url": "https://juniperspring.org/posts/honda-evil-valet/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/bt3cq8",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "hoistbypetard",
      "published": "2026-06-17T02:59:20Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Unrestricted OBD-II port access allows attackers to program unauthorized key fobs in under five minutes using readily available locksmith tools.",
        "Honda vehicles suffer from rolling code bypasses like CVE-2022-27254, enabling attackers to capture and replay RF signals to unlock doors.",
        "Securing vehicles requires physical OBD port locks and RF-shielding pouches, as standard valet modes lack cryptographic hardware isolation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "What job interviews taught me about Kubernetes",
      "url": "https://notnotp.com/notes/what-job-interviews-taught-me-about-kubernetes/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/k6qon4",
      "score": 43,
      "comments": 52,
      "author": "rau",
      "published": "2026-06-16T02:41:09Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Many organizations adopt Kubernetes prematurely when simpler alternatives like AWS ECS, Nomad, or systemd services would reduce operational overhead.",
        "Interviews reveal a critical gap in fundamental K8s networking (CNIs like Calico, CoreDNS) and storage internals over simple YAML templating.",
        "Production troubleshooting skills, including Prometheus monitoring, RBAC security, and debugging etcd consistency, are far more valued than basic deployment automation."
      ]
    },
